The paper focuses on failure-oblivious computing, which is a technique used to achieve high availability of software systems. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves analyzing the behavior of software systems, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or computer networks and communications (cs.CR). The experiment performed in the paper involves computing the search space of failures, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or systems and control (cs.SY).
